rage door opener may cause the door or trolley to bind up-causing the opener to stop or reverse because opening or closing force exceeded the openers force limit.";i:53;s:59:"Cold weather can affect safety sensors in a number of ways.";i:54;s:126:"When there is an issue with your safety sensors the opener will interpret this as an obstruction and refuse to close the door.";i:55;s:151:"If the issue is with the sensors youll likely find that you can use the garage door remote or wall-mounted switch to open the door but not to close it.";i:56;s:19:"Cause and Solution.";i:57;s:109:"This is usually a problem that is related to the safety sensors you have that control the garage door opener.";i:58;s:82:"If the sensors detect something in the way they will not allow the doors to close.";i:59;s:66:"When it is extremely hot it can cause these sensors t malfunction.";}}